title: Myanmar Signs Cease-Fire With Several Rebel Groups Ahead of Elections
text:
YANGONâ€”Myanmar signed a cease-fire on Thursday with several ethnic rebel groups, but some of them had long stopped fighting and several others refused to come on board, denying the government a needed political boost three weeks before national elections, as sporadic conflicts continued.
In a grandiose ceremony in the capital Naypyitaw, representatives of the eight armed groups sat alongside military generals and Myanmar President...
